    "body": "I'm having the same issue... Traced it back to `Artifactor.prototype.saveAll`\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\n  if (Array.isArray(objects)) {\r\n    var array = objects;\r\n    objects = {};\r\n\r\n    array.forEach(function(item) {\r\n      objects[item.contract_name] = item;\r\n    })\r\n  }\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is problematic if you have 2 contracts with the same `contract_name`, even if you aren't using them! For example, if you have `zeppelin-solidity` installed via NPM, it has a `Migrations` contract, and you might have a `Migrations` contract as well.\r\n\r\nIn this case, one of these contracts have `.networks` sections like this:\r\n\r\n`zeppelin-solidity/contracts/lifecycle/Migrations.sol`:\r\n```\r\n{ '5777':\r\n   { events: {},\r\n     links: {},\r\n     address: '0x...' } }\r\n```\r\n\r\n`./Migrations.sol`:\r\n```\r\n{}\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen the array is flattened to an object, they both have the name `Migrations`, thus only the second one is ever acted upon.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure that this is correct?",
